Item.Heading: FLOOR
Item.Notepad2:
Easily the most authentic timber-look porcelain floor tiles available in the world, this material will have you doubting your own eyes! Is it really a tile? It must surely be timber ...
Produced in Italy using the latest HIGH-DEFINITION digital-print technology, glaze is intricately applied to the tile surface to faithfully re-create all the detail, graining & nuances of natural timber -- delivering the maximum possible pattern variation to these first quality tiles.
These tiles have been tested as having an R11 slip-resistant surface, making them ideal for use not only internally, but also externally on decks, pathways & driveways. Being porcelain, the greatest advantage these tiles have over natural timber is they won't warp, crack or fade and NEVER need to be sanded or sealed/treated/coated, making them a true "set-and-forget" flooring option!
Two tile size options are available: 800x200mm and 800x130mm, which can be laid integrated (50/50 mixed) or as a single type. Sells with a Tax Invoice and we're happy to help with any technical or installation advice you may need. The quality of these tiles is outstanding and potential buyers are definitely encouraged to inspect this material.

GOBI CAFE PLATINA BLANCO KALAHARI ANTHRACITE
All the above colours are available in 3 main sizes: 300x300mm, 300x600mm and 600x600mm (plus the made-to-order size: 150x150mm @ $68.30/sqm available upon request). Sells with a Tax Invoice and we're happy to help with any technical or other installation advice you may need for your particular project. Feel free to contact us with any questions about this range.
